    {
      "title": "Experiment \\operatorname{Exp}_{A,\\Pi}^{\\operatorname{anon}}(\\lambda)\n\npp \\leftarrow \\operatorname{Setup}(1^{\\lambda}), b \\leftarrow^{\\$} \\{0,1\\}, (pk,st) \\leftarrow \\mathcal{A}(pp)\n\nRegisterKeys(pk), (u_0, upk_0), (u_1, upk_1) \\leftarrow \\operatorname{Keygen}()\n\nst \\leftarrow \\mathcal{A}^{\\operatorname{Join}(\\cdot),\\operatorname{Earn}(\\cdot,\\cdot),\\operatorname{Spend}(\\cdot,\\cdot,\\cdot)}(st,u_0, upk_0,u_1, upk_1)\n\nb' \\leftarrow \\mathcal{A}^{\\operatorname{Earn}(u_b,\\cdot),\\operatorname{Spend}(u_b,\\cdot,\\cdot)}(st)\n\nwhere \\mathcal{A} is restricted to a single oracle query, and:\n\nIf \\mathcal{A} calls \\operatorname{Earn}(u_b,\\cdot) on input k,\n\\nif \\max\\{v_{u_0},v_{u_1}\\}>v_{max} or \\bot\\in\\{token_{u_0},token_{u_1}\\}\n\nor (mustRetry_{u_0},mustRetry_{u_1})\\neq(\\bot,\\bot), output 0.\n\nIf \\mathcal{A} calls \\operatorname{Spend}(u_b,\\cdot,\\cdot) on input k,tid,\n\\nif \\min\\{v_{u_0},v_{u_1}\\}< k or \\bot\\in\\{token_{u_0},token_{u_1}\\}\n\nor (mustRetry_{u_0},mustRetry_{u_1})\\neq(\\bot,\\bot), output 0.\n\nreturn 1 iff b=b'",
      "heading_level": null,
      "page_id": 10,
      "polygon": [
        [
          180.791015625,
          91.65234375
        ],
        [
          425.25,
          91.65234375
        ],
        [
          425.25,
          236.25
        ],
        [
          180.791015625,
          236.25
        ]
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Experiment Expadv-fr\nA,B,Π(λ)\npp ← Setup(1λ\n), pk ← ProviderKeyGen(), RegisterKeys(pk)\n(st, upkA) ← A(pp, pk)\nRun st0 ← AIssue(upkA)\n(st) (require that A queries the oracle exactly once)\nRun A\nCredit(·),Deduct(·,·),DBsync(·)\n(pp, pk, st0\n) and\nB\nIssue(·),Credit(·),Deduct(·,·),DBsync(·)\n(pp, pk, upkA) in parallel\n(note that A and B cannot communicate with each other, but their\noracles work on the same state).\nreturn 1 iff there is transaction tid with predecessor dsid in DB such that\ndsid is associated with upkA but\nthe transaction id tid does not belong to one of A's Deduct queries.",
